A BILL FORAN ACT
RELATING TO RURAL EMERGENCY HOSPITALS.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the federal
2 government has recently authorized the creation of rural
3 emergency hospitals, a new type of medicare provider meant to
4 help address the concerning increase in rural hospital closures
5 nationwide. Rural emergency hospitals provide rural communities
6 with emergency department services, observation care, and
7 tailored outpatient medical and health services, including
8 laboratory and imaging services. By adopting the rural
9 emergency hospital designation, a hospital can focus on these
10 important services while eliminating certain high-cost services
11 that the community is not utilizing, such as inpatient care.
12 This focus allows the hospital to allocate its limited resources
13 to better address needs of the community the hospital serves.
14 The legislature further finds that the creation of the
15 rural emergency hospital designation may be beneficial to the
16 financial health of certain hospitals and the communities they
17 serve. By adopting a rural emergency hospital designation, a
