8 The legislature notes that each rural emergency hospital is
9 responsible for meeting higher-level patient care needs by
10 having transfer agreements with local trauma centers.
11 The legislature finds that the federal government designed
12 the rural emergency hospital designation for hospitals like
13 Lanai community hospital, to allow those hospitals to best meet
14 the health care needs of their communities by emphasizing
15 emergency services, long-term care, and skilled nursing.
